declaring their mystification over
the systematic murder of millions.

6
00:00:39,593 --> 00:00:43,723
The reason why they can never answer
the question "How could it happen?"

7
00:00:43,848 --> 00:00:45,768
is that it's the wrong question.

8
00:00:45,893 --> 00:00:49,815
Given what people are, the question is
"Why doesn't it happen more often?"

9
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:55,322
- Of course, it does, in subtler forms.
- I have a headache from this weather.

10
00:00:58,576 --> 00:01:01,788
It's been ages since
I sat in front of the TV,

11
00:01:01,914 --> 00:01:04,709
just changing channels to find something.

12
00:01:04,834 --> 00:01:07,170
You see the whole culture:

13
00:01:07,295 --> 00:01:09,548
Nazis, deodorant salesmen,

14
00:01:10,466 --> 00:01:13,762
wrestlers, beauty contests,
the talk show...

15
00:01:14,597 --> 00:01:18,518
Can you imagine the level of
a mind that watches wrestling?

16
00:01:18,643 --> 00:01:23,692
But the worst are the fundamentalist
preachers: third-rate con men

17
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:27,405
telling the poor suckers that watch them
that they speak for Jesus.

18
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:31,034
And to please send in money.
Money, money, money.

19
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:35,540
If Jesus came back and saw
what's going on in his name,

20
00:01:35,665 --> 00:01:39,796
- he'd never stop throwing up.
- Oh, God, would you please lighten up?

21
00:01:39,921 --> 00:01:44,469
I'm really not in the mood to hear
a review of contemporary society again.

22
00:01:45,637 --> 00:01:49,308
- You've been very nervous lately.
- I can't take this any more.

23
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:52,437
I'm trying to complete an education
I started five years ago.

24
00:01:52,604 --> 00:01:55,149
I'm not your pupil. I was, but I'm not.

25
00:01:55,316 --> 00:01:58,737
When you leave the nest, I want you
to be ready to face the real world.

26
00:01:58,904 --> 00:02:01,115
We're going to have to
make some changes.

27
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:04,328
- Like what?
- You know what. I'm suffocating.

28
00:02:04,453 --> 00:02:09,125
- Are we having this conversation again?
- Yes, we are having it again.

29
00:02:09,292 --> 00:02:12,421
- I have to leave. I have to move out.
- Why?

30
00:02:12,588 --> 00:02:15,884
- Because I have to.
- What are you going to use for money?

31
00:02:16,009 --> 00:02:19,556
I don't know. I thought maybe I'd
move in with my parents for a while.

32
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:24,437
I always told you you would leave me.
Does it have to be now?

33
00:02:24,562 --> 00:02:27,900
Maybe it'll only be temporary,
but I have to try.

34
00:02:28,025 --> 00:02:31,112
Oh, Lee. You are my whole world.

35
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:38,413
Good God. Have you been kissed tonight?

36
00:02:38,538 --> 00:02:40,916
- No.
- Oh, yes, you have.

37
00:02:41,042 --> 00:02:43,587
- You've been with someone!
- Stop accusing me!

38
00:02:43,712 --> 00:02:45,881
I'm too smart, Lee. You can't fool me!

39
00:02:46,006 --> 00:02:48,092
- You're turning all red.
- Leave me alone!

40
00:02:48,218 --> 00:02:50,679
Christ, what's wrong with you?

41
00:02:53,349 --> 00:02:56,228
- I'm sorry.
- Couldn't you say something?

42
00:02:56,353 --> 00:02:59,983
- You have to slither behind my back...
- I'm saying it now!

43
00:03:00,108 --> 00:03:02,152
So you met somebody else?

44
00:03:03,154 --> 00:03:04,155
Yeah.

45
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:08,494
But you knew it was going to happen
sooner or later. I can't live like this!

46
00:03:08,619 --> 00:03:11,915
- Who is it?
- What's the difference? Somebody I met.

47
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:16,296
- But who? Where did you meet him?
- It doesn't matter. I have to move out.

48
00:03:16,421 --> 00:03:18,882
You are my only connection to the world.

49
00:03:19,007 --> 00:03:23,054
Oh, God, that's too much
responsibility for me. It's not fair!

50
00:03:23,179 --> 00:03:26,100
I want a less complicated life.
I want a husband,

51
00:03:26,225 --> 00:03:30,439
- maybe even a child, before it's too late.
- Jesus! Jesus!

52
00:03:30,564 --> 00:03:33,443
Oh, God, I don't even know what I want.

53
00:03:36,488 --> 00:03:39,576
What do you get out of me,
anyway? I mean...

54
00:03:40,994 --> 00:03:43,289
It's not sexual any more.

55
00:03:44,373 --> 00:03:48,212
It's certainly not intellectual.
You're so superior to me in every way...

56
00:03:48,337 --> 00:03:50,381
Don't patronise me!

57
00:03:51,883 --> 00:03:57,349
God, I should have married you
years ago, when you wanted to.

58
00:03:57,474 --> 00:04:01,479
- I should have agreed.
- It never would have worked.

59
00:04:03,315 --> 00:04:07,445
I told you one day you would
leave me for a younger man. I...

60
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:22,005
What passion today with Lee!
She's a volcano.

61
00:04:23,215 --> 00:04:27,763
It was a totally fulfilling experience,
just as I'd dreamed it would be.

62
00:04:27,888 --> 00:04:32,477
That's what it was. It was like
living out a dream. A great dream.

63
00:04:33,562 --> 00:04:37,150
Now I feel very good and cosy
being here next to Hannah.

64
00:04:37,275 --> 00:04:40,029
There's something very lovely
and real about Hannah.

65
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:44,743
She gives me a very deep feeling
of being part of something.

66
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:48,915
She's a wonderful woman...
and I betrayed her.

67
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:51,669
She came into my empty life
and changed it,

68
00:04:51,794 --> 00:04:55,507
and I paid her back by
banging her sister in a hotel room.

69
00:04:55,632 --> 00:04:59,721
God, I'm despicable.
What a cruel and shallow thing to do.

70
00:04:59,846 --> 00:05:02,266
I have to call her and say
what we did was crazy.

71
00:05:02,391 --> 00:05:06,605
It can't happen again. I'm not that kind
of man, and I value Hannah too much.

72
00:05:06,730 --> 00:05:10,318
I love my wife.
Now I betrayed her. Oh, God!

73
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:14,699
- Where are you going?
- I've, uh, got to get a phone number.

74
00:05:14,824 --> 00:05:17,244
- I forgot to phone Mel Kaufman.
- It's so late.

75
00:05:17,410 --> 00:05:19,413
Yeah, I can't believe I forgot.

76
00:05:20,539 --> 00:05:23,293
If he answers, I'll hang up.

77
00:05:23,418 --> 00:05:28,091
I'll tell her we can't communicate until
I terminate my marriage. It's immoral.

78
00:05:28,216 --> 00:05:32,346
Then time will pass, I won't call,
and she'll get the idea.

79
00:05:32,472 --> 00:05:35,142
Gotta stop this before I get in too deep.

80
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:39,355
I'd rather hurt Lee a little
than destroy Hannah.

81
00:05:39,481 --> 00:05:44,362
It's 1.30. She can't have a conversation
with me with him around.

82
00:05:44,487 --> 00:05:46,615
I'm getting hysterical.

83
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:49,076
I'll call her first thing in the morning.

84
00:05:49,201 --> 00:05:50,870
I'll call her at six.

85
00:05:50,995 --> 00:05:55,877
Frederick goes jogging at six.
I'll call her and nip it in the bud.

86
00:05:56,002 --> 00:05:57,003
(phone rings)

87
00:05:57,170 --> 00:05:59,214
I've got it! I've got it!

88
00:06:00,132 --> 00:06:01,676
Hello?

89
00:06:01,801 --> 00:06:03,261
Mel!

90
00:06:03,386 --> 00:06:06,808
I would have hung up if you hadn't
answered and I won't do this again,

91
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:10,854
but I just had to tell you...
I feel very close to you tonight.

92
00:06:11,021 --> 00:06:13,233
Very, very close.

93
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:15,193
Good night.

94
00:06:29,295 --> 00:06:32,674
