00:46:14,795 --> 00:46:19,676
So you wanna go out to dinner again?
Do you have any interest in that?

673
00:46:19,801 --> 00:46:23,139
- Sure.
- Are you free this evening?

674
00:46:23,264 --> 00:46:25,267
Yeah, yeah.

675
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:33,611
I want ice! Who's got some?

676
00:46:33,778 --> 00:46:35,321
Oh, there it is.

677
00:46:35,446 --> 00:46:37,491
Hey, where's Holly? She's late.

678
00:46:37,658 --> 00:46:40,536
Did you read Holly's last thing?
She's really developed.

679
00:46:40,662 --> 00:46:42,706
She really writes good dialogue.

680
00:46:42,873 --> 00:46:45,334
Hannah, can I say you're
going to play Desdemona?

681
00:46:45,501 --> 00:46:49,006
- Mom, it's only television.
- But it's public television.

682
00:46:49,131 --> 00:46:52,135
To me, Shakespeare doesn't
get any greater than Othello.

683
00:46:52,302 --> 00:46:56,515
- You with some big, black stud. I love it!
- Oh, honey!

684
00:47:22,424 --> 00:47:25,428
(Elliot) Oh, Lee. You are something.

685
00:47:26,512 --> 00:47:30,643
You look very beautiful.
Marriage agrees with you.

686
00:47:32,979 --> 00:47:37,944
Everything that happened between us
seems more and more hazy.

687
00:47:39,321 --> 00:47:43,451
I acted like such a fool.
I don't know what came over me.

688
00:47:44,035 --> 00:47:47,999
The complete conviction
that I couldn't live without you.

689
00:47:48,666 --> 00:47:51,044
What I put us both through!

690
00:47:51,169 --> 00:47:56,343
And Hannah, who, as you once said,
I love much more than I realised.

691
00:48:00,223 --> 00:48:03,811
Hi! Happy Thanksgiving!

692
00:48:05,187 --> 00:48:09,026
- Hi, Daisy. I didn't miss dinner, did I?
- No.

693
00:48:09,151 --> 00:48:12,238
Hi, Marge. Happy Thanksgiving!

694
00:48:12,363 --> 00:48:15,451
Happy Thanksgiving, Amy.

695
00:48:15,576 --> 00:48:18,455
(# piano playing "Isn't It Romantic")

696
00:49:16,613 --> 00:49:18,657
It's beautiful.

697
00:49:22,204 --> 00:49:24,290
- Don't be nervous. It's your husband.
- Hi.

698
00:49:24,415 --> 00:49:26,125
- Hi. How are you doing?
- OK.

699
00:49:26,251 --> 00:49:28,921
- When did you get here?
- Just a few minutes ago.

700
00:49:29,046 --> 00:49:31,257
- You look so beautiful.
- Thanks.

701
00:49:31,382 --> 00:49:35,721
I was talking to your father before.
I was telling him that it's ironic.

702
00:49:35,846 --> 00:49:38,600
I used to always have
Thanksgiving with Hannah.

703
00:49:38,725 --> 00:49:42,104
I never thought that
I could love anybody else.

704
00:49:42,230 --> 00:49:47,820
And here it is, years later, and I'm married
to you, and completely in love with you.

705
00:49:47,945 --> 00:49:51,950
The heart is a very,
very resilient little muscle.

706
00:49:54,078 --> 00:49:59,168
It would make a great story, I think. A guy
marries one sister and it doesn't work out.

707
00:49:59,293 --> 00:50:04,425
Then, years later,
he winds up married to the other sister.

708
00:50:04,592 --> 00:50:07,470
I don't know how you're gonna top that.

709
00:50:08,597 --> 00:50:10,641
- Mickey?
- What?

710
00:50:12,018 --> 00:50:14,062
I'm pregnant.

711
00:53:27,646 --> 00:53:31,943
